description: The head of Germany's public health agency says people have been "negligent" as infections increase.
title: Coronavirus: German officials 'very concerned' by rising cases
title_page: Coronavirus: German officials 'very concerned' by rising cases - BBC News
maintext: "We don't know yet if this is the beginning of a second wave but of course it could be," Mr Wieler said. "But I am optimistic that if we follow the hygiene rules we can prevent it, it's up to us."
